The article announces various nominations and appointments made by the President. Some of the key appointments include Thomas S. Andrews as Special Assistant to the President for Legislative Affairs, Robert B. Blair as Assistant to the President and Senior Advisor to the Chief of Staff, Monica J. Block as Deputy Assistant to the President and Director of White House Management and Administration, and Pat A. Cipollone as Assistant to the President and Counsel to the President. Other appointees include individuals for positions such as Deputy Director of Trade and Manufacturing Policy, Director of Operations for the Office of the First Lady, Principal Deputy Chief of Staff, Deputy Counsel to the President for National Security Affairs, and many more.